enum Feature::FeatureAttributeId [inherited]
 

When an attribute (property) of a feature has been changed, the message FeatureChangedMsg will be send. The message contains a property-index, which indicates the attribute property or attribute-group. The attribute-indices 0 to 99 are reserved for APOXI. Additional defined ids:

  • 2: Property::ValueAttributeId
Enumerator:
UnspecifiedAttributeId  Not every property must have its own id. In this case UnspecifiedPropertyId may be used.
AvailableAttributeId 
EnabledAttributeId 
CustomAttributeId

void Feature::BlockNotification (  BOOLEAN  block  )  [inline, inherited]
 

If block is TRUE, sending of FeatureChangedMsg in case of a state change is blocked. This might be useful when the feature-providing application needs to update the state of a set of features, whereby notification should be supressed. Per default the notification is not blocked.
